    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Sep 18. 1838</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I have duly received yr esteemed Favors of<lb/>
                <sic>of</sic> the <date>9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Aug.</date> &amp; <date>5<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi></date> Inst, &amp; regret much to find that yr health is
                so<lb/> precarious. The parcel for <persName>Mr Benjamin</persName> pr S C. is at
                hand &amp; shall be<lb/> forwarded by first conveyance: that pr
                    <persName>Randoph</persName> has never been received, indeed<lb/> I knew nothing
                of it until after the Schooner had left yr request as to<lb/> the contribution by a
                young Lady of yr flock for rebuilding synagogue<lb/> will be most <add>?</add>
                <sic>fullfilling</sic>. My time my dear Sir does not<lb/> allow me to be as full in
                my correspondence with you as I could wish..<lb/> I would most willingly give you
                all the aid I could for carrying out<lb/> yr zealous &amp; highly praiseworthy
                efforts in the cause of our holy religion<lb/> were I differently circumstanced but
                I have but a very small fraction<lb/> of time to devote even to my family, as to my
                Father his time<lb/> is so much engrossed with congregational duties,
                    increased<add>?</add> much<lb/> by the epidemic which has been raging in our
                city, that he<lb/> I am sure, could not give that attention to the holy work
                necessary<lb/> I would therefore suggest the propriety of yr opening a
                correspondence<lb/> with a highly reputable gentleman of our congregation, one
                of<lb/> much leisure &amp; sufficient val<add>?</add>. I refer to <persName>Major I.
                    Lazarus</persName>, who is<lb/> one of the Trustees of the Syngagogue. I do
                think he will with much<lb/> pleasure take charge of those duties which have been in
                our<lb/> hands, &amp; all such which may be necessary to carry out yr zealous</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>efforts to enlighten the <add>?</add> generation of Israelites in the<lb/> principles
                of our holy religion. I trust that you will view<lb/> this suggestion of change only
                in a friendly light We<lb/> are unable from circumstances to do that justice to your
                calls<lb/> which our feelings prompt <del>as well</del> &amp; which they richly
                merit<lb/> our Hazan has had leave of absence in consequence of the unhealthy<lb/>
                condition of our city, a very large number of strangers have fallen<lb/> victims
                among whom some few of <placeName>Israel</placeName>: <persName>Mr
                    Poznanski</persName> is at<lb/> present in <placeName>Greenville
                    SoCa.</placeName> comfortably situated on his return I will<lb/> place in his
                hands yr two last letters &amp; doubt not they will <sic>received</sic><lb/> due
                attention. With my best wishes that the ensuing year<lb/> will be one full of good
                to you &amp; all <placeName>Israel</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">yr Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">I. N. Hart</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Pastor Hebrew Congregation</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>single</p>
            <p>
                <persName>Smith Moury</persName>
                <add>?</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">agent</p>
        </body>
